Somewhere in the South Pacific...
0950 Zulu

The calm seas are awash with blood, salt, and poison. The sky is filled with bright tracers screaming towards fiber wings. Alas! It is another day in the life of the Kommando. The sands of Clamshell Island will stain red, for the Scarlets wish to destroy the Azure's radio tower, obliterate their bunker, and raze the local supply of 'happy plant.'

Ocean Gliders: Hold LMB to glide, search for the seagull wind updrafts as they will provide altitude. (Video Tutorial will be made available soon)

RC Heli: Hold LMB to climb, RMB to detonate. The control panel is inside of the Azure Kommando bunker. The dynamite is fragile and cannot take a direct hit from anything!

Naval Vessels: Sub is below barge, boats play tunes with LMB, detach with RMB.

Flamethrower: The flamethrower is activated with RMB. Beware, it takes away a substantial amount of health in order to use this powerful device. This was meant to keep the gameplay fairly balanced.

Secrets: 

Flamethrower - Located on top of the Azure Kommando's bunker.
RC Heli - A well placed grenade can knock out that pesky beast easily.
Scout - Located on a small rocky outcropping on the beach, the scout is only accessible to those who can fly or by anyone smart enough to knock it off with a grenade.
Awp - Located atop the high radio tower, the awp is accessible to only the most skilled of hang glider pilots!
Submarine - Tired of becoming RC Heli bait? Why not go under the waves to reach your final destination! The infantry submarine is located directly under the Scarlet Kommando barge.

Tips: 

Machine guns keeping you off the stairs? Don't fret! Throw a grenade. Out of grenades? Get back to the docks where unlimited grenade spawns are available.

Don't drop the soap.



Map by: Butterknife (Jaekto)
Misc: Shiroko

TO PASS THE CRANE PART, YOU MUST NOT TOUCH THE PANEL. KEEP IN THE MIDDLE OF THE PLATFORM. THE LEFT BUTTON MOVES LEFT/RIGHT. THE MIDDLE BUTTON MOVES THE CRANE ARM UP/DOWN. THIS MAP IS INTENDED FOR SINGLE-PLAYER EXPERIENCES, although you can play with a friend or two. Don't put this on large servers. In 2012, CERN launched the LHC experiment to full power. As most expected, the experiment went wrong and Earth suffered with it. The fissure destroyed constructions and drained all Earth oceans. Humanity's last hope is a colonization ship being sent to Kepler. The Keystone IV Voyager will follow the Kepler precursor Viper2. Your assignment is to launch the three Vipers today.
A contest is always a motivation to map. Not only because there are winners or loses, but because people give feedback. Last time I joined one was the LHC mapping contest and the pros and cons surprised me. With that feedback, I made this map. I took me a while to find the right resources. As always, I focused on effects and cinematics. But I also wanted to give some control to the player. It is not just push the button and launch the rocket. You must open the fuel valves, use the crane to attach the spaceship to the rocket, and so on. I'm pretty satisfyed with how this ended up. I hope you all enjoy!

A Fun mg map where both teams spawn across a field with knives and try to knife the other team while the ground breaks off opening up crevices that players fall through to a lava death. Its fast paced rounds and fun randomness. The crevices open up randomly between 5 and 20 seconds so the map is a bit random each round making it entertaining. The more people the more fun it is when they all fall through a crack. Took 45 minutes to make. (Spawns set up for 20v20 so go crazy with the server size)

mg_ka_trains_detach_evo

 Hello, I remade this map, by adding something to make it more mg_ ....
Modes.

The mapmaker of mg_ka_trains_detach tried to do something like this but forgot some output in an entity ^^

Modes

 The map is split into 2 globals "modes".
Per default, the mode is "Fun", and got 10 modes possible.
In the other mode you can only play Normal & Autobhop (which need a plugin i included)
  • Normal (like the old ka_trains_detach)
  • Autobhop (it needs the infinite-jumping plugin you can find at https://forums.alliedmods.net/showthread.php?p=1239361 or in the file)
  • Drug (everyone is drugged and get some colors on the screen (it use sm_drug command)
  • Low Grav (you get low gravity)
  • Blind (your screen became almost black (it uses sm_blind 230 command) )
  • ScoutKnivez (give you scout and low gravity)
  • 1 HP mode
  • 200 HP mode
  • Big players (it's 2x Size)
  • Little players (its mini size)
  • Mushroom Drug (you get a drugged screen)

Some Skins

 CT get a random big-head skin every round and T get a random big-head skin every round.

Some Musics

 Music is played automatically in "Fun" Mode
  • El mudo - Chacarron Macarron
  • Matrix Futurebound ft. Luke Bingham - All i know
  • Benny Hill - Theme
  • Darude - SandStorm
  • Scatman
  • Titanic Flute
  • Le Internet Medlay
  • Chineese Music

How to change mode

 If you are admin, just noclip to the room with dev-texture colored.
  • Button at the right to enable "Fun" Mode
  • Button at the left to enable "Classic" Mode
If no admins on, you can go there, by first going in the skybox using a teleporter there: And then press a "secret" button on the ground (check the edge of the skybox to see it). When you go in the skybox, your skin become a daft punk skin.

Enjoy
